<rubyforge xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Contact</title>

  <page>
    <xi:include href="_menu.xml" />

    <content>
      <section label="contact" title="Contact">
        <subsection label="email" title="Email">
          <p>I can be contacted with specific questions or comments relating to <project-title /> at the following email address: <project-email />.</p>
        </subsection>

        <subsection label="irc" title="IRC">
          <p>
            Ronin also has a dedicated IRC channel for general questions or
            feedback. Simply join <b>#ronin</b> on
            <a href="http://freenode.net/">irc.freenode.net</a>.
          </p>

          <p>
            If you don't have an IRC client, you can use freenode's Java
            Chat Applet
            <a href="http://java.freenode.net/index.php?channel=ronin">here</a>.
          </p>
        </subsection>

        <subsection label="jabber" title="Jabber">
          <p>
            IRC not to your liking? Do you prefer Instant Messaging instead?
            Ronin also has a persistant Jabber channel available on
            <a href="http://jabber.org/">jabber.org</a>.
          </p>

          <p>
            Simply join the <kbd>ronin</kbd> chat-room on
            <kbd>conference.jabber.org</kbd>.
          </p>
        </subsection>
      </section>
    </content>
  </page>
</rubyforge>
